# Layer boundaries

## Import rules

- `app/` **never** imports from `server/` (directly or via `@/server/...`).
- Shared contracts live in `shared/` (HTTP helpers, Oshima schemas, quadkeys).
- Browser HTTP lives in `app/adapter/http.adapter.ts` (`ApiHttp` Context.Service + `BrowserHttpClient`; provide `ApiHttp.Live` via `app/runtime/api-http.runtime.ts`).
- Browser Translator API lives in `app/adapter/translation.adapter.ts` (`TranslatorApi`; provide via `app/runtime/translator-api.runtime.ts`).
- Browser persistence + geolocation live in `app/store` via `Atom.kvs` / `browserAtomRuntime` (`BrowserKeyValueStore` + `Geolocation`).
- Domain TanStack Query options live in `app/query/domain.query.ts` (subscribe with `useQuery`, imperatively `ensureQueryData`).
- Domain HTTP calls + mapping live in `app/repository/`.
- `server/controller/http/*.http.ts` is Worker/upstream only.
- Enforce with `bun run check:boundaries`.

## Data flow

```
container/hook ← useQuery / ensureQueryData (app/query) + usecase
    ↑
usecase   ← repository (HTTP/Translator) or store (Atom.kvs / Geolocation)
    ↑
repository ← yield* ApiHttp / TranslatorApi + domain mapping
store      ← browserAtomRuntime (KeyValueStore + Geolocation)
    ↑
app/adapter/*.adapter.ts (Context.Service + Layer)
```

Provide Layers only at the runtime edge (`ManagedRuntime` / `Atom.runtime`). Do not `Effect.provide` inside adapters, repositories, or stores. Usecase never imports adapters directly.
